Example in the console:

var d = Date.parseDate("12/Asd/13", "%d/%m/%Y");
console.log(d);

Will print:
Sat Oct 12 2013 00:00:00 GMT+1100 (EST)

This is due to line 1752 of Calendar.js: if (isNaN(m)) m = today.getMonth();

It is autocorrecting invalid input but not providing the caller with any error or indication that this occurred.

----

The same occur with the other units year, date, hours and minutes.

